# MobX stores (`@comfort-b2b/mobile`)

One store per file (a class), co-located `*.test.ts`. Live in
`packages/mobile/src/stores`. `RootStore` is the composition root that wires the
others and owns the cart→analytics `reaction`.

## Dependency-inject the API, never import it into a store
Stores take their API functions (`fetchCatalog`/`sendAnalytics`/`submitOrder`)
as constructor params (function-typed), and inter-store deps (e.g. the catalog)
as params too. `RootStore` takes an `ApiDeps` object; the composition root in
`App.tsx` passes the real `apiClient` functions. **Reason:** importing
`apiClient` pulls in `config.ts` → `react-native-config`, which throws on the
missing `API_BASE_URL` in the Jest node env. DI keeps stores out of that chain so
they unit-test with plain mocks (no RN preset, no react-native-config stub).

## mobx + TypeScript `private` fields
`keyof this` excludes `private`/`protected` members, so a private field can't be
named in `makeAutoObservable`'s typed annotations map without help. Pass the key
via the `AdditionalKeys` generic:

```ts
makeAutoObservable<CartStore, "catalog">(this, { catalog: false });
```

Assign injected deps to regular declared fields in the constructor body (NOT
constructor parameter properties) before calling `makeAutoObservable`/
`makeObservable` — parameter properties are likewise absent from `keyof this`.

## Use `makeObservable` when there's non-observable plumbing
A store with queues/counters/timers (e.g. `AnalyticsStore`) uses explicit
`makeObservable` listing ONLY the observable state + the `action` methods;
everything else stays plain. Always wrap observable mutations that run **after
an `await`** (or from a `setTimeout`) in `runInAction`.

## Analytics delivery contract
`AnalyticsStore` is a reliable queue, not a fire-and-forget call: debounce rapid
edits into one event, deliver strictly in order, retry with bounded exponential
backoff, guard the rolled-up `lastStatus` with a monotonic `seq` (an older /
manually-retried delivery must never clobber a newer event's status), keep an
audit log (`records`), and send the FULL denormalized product+option list every
time.
